                    <span>This book is more than a guide to swimming. It's a guide to understanding how teach your body swimming as if it were a language. I used it myself and found a pleasure in swimming that I previously had not found, the result has been a quick transition from beginner to intermediate freestyle swimmer. The book is not perfect, it repeats itself (in fact this may be the mantra that makes the book so appealing), also I found the drills difficult to interpret from print. Even so, I found the book everything I needed to make me realise that swimming is an endless search for a beautiful perfection.
<br />Andy Fallows</span>
                  
